[div class=p 
	"This submission is 3763 input frames faster than 
	(__wikiLink|displaytext=the previous submission|href=/7826S)
	" for this game. Most of that is from ending input very early in the final race.  If the race were played out, it would be 684 frames faster.
	$LF
]div
[h3 id=RaceByRaceComments 
	" Race by Race comments:
	$LF
]h3
[div class=p 
	[b 
		"Race 1
	]b
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"You want to get the turbo in the first helicopter drop to increase max speed from 170 to 180, then you just need to get gas upgrades.  Note that landing on the truck is key here, you don't use gas while on it, and you would run out before the finish if you didn't. Note that the 2nd turbo gotten at the end does nothing in terms of time, no upgrade is advantageous there.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"50 frames improved by manipulating the gas upgrades without slowing down
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	[b 
		"Race 2
	]b
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Slick tires are picked as the upgrade, so getting a turbo does not help.  So it is just a matter of getting gas upgrades. Note that getting a regular gas instead of a high gas is not enough gas, so it seems you have to end with 2 bars of gas
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	[b 
		"Race 3
	]b
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Getting brock tires is necessary here.  As such, you want to get the turbo as soon as possible.  236 frames improved here by getting gas while getting a turbo drop.  This effectively reduces how much time is spent not having turbo.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Note that it would be faster to get turbo from the 1st helicopter drop but it seems to be impossible to get one there.  Some drops have all the possible outcomes but this one is limited, even the helpers are impossible, which are very common normally.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"There is an alternate strategy to avoid getting gas.  You slow down during the 2nd helicopter drop instead of stopping to get gas.  It manipulates a 3rd helicopter.  You get gas from both and you no longer need a pit stop.  However, it is slower overall by about 100 frames.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"The invulnerability drop is just for swag.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	[b 
		"_Bonus Race
	]b
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"This race is unavoidable, and you want to crash as soon as possible.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"4 frames saved by not picking an upgrade since it does not affect the race and you lose it afterwards.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	[b 
		"Race 4
	]b
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"354 frames saved here by slowing down on to make the 2nd helicopter drop not fall into the river.  This allows me to get a gas upgrade and avoid a pit stop.  It seems unfortunate to have to end the race with 4 bars of gas, but getting a low gas just barely misses the finish line.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	[b 
		"Race 5
	]b
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"The early input here is just insane.  First, you need slick tires and a turbo.  While this does not help on max speed, it does affect resting (non-input speed) by bumping it from 80 to 99.  This is enough speed that cares will not catch up from behind.  Next is to manipulate luck to get a very nice rank early on and get as many cars to crash as possible.  Next is to manipulate the final care before input end to not move over in front of you.  Then a hi gas must be manipulated 2 helicopters later.  At that point there is a magic x position of 96 that somehow avoid all obstacles, causes every car to spawn on obstacles, AND picks up the high gas upgrade to have enough gas to finish the race!
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Note that it might seem like an invulnerability on the first helicopter would allow even earlier input but then your resting speed is only 80 and cars will catch up and if not kill you, then cause you to place to low to count.
	$LF
]div
