[div class=p 
	[a class=intlink href=/Users/Profile/ThunderAxe31 
		"ThunderAxe31
	]a
	": Beating the second loop results in displaying the game ending screen. However, from what I could see in my tests, the second loop si completely redundant. Even the first stage of the second loop resulted exactly the same, despite the ability to select upgrades that aren't available at the beginning of the game. So it just makes sense to raise an exception and consider the first loop sufficient, just like the relative RTA 
	[a href=https://www.speedrun.com/rally_bike rel=noopener external nofollow 
		"community
	]a
	" do.
	$LF
]div
